'''Shōni Suketoki''' (少弐 資時) was a mid-{{ill|Kamakura period|ja|鎌倉時代|qq=draft|qq=draft}} {{ill|samurai|ja|武士|qq=draft|qq=draft}} and the eldest son of {{ill|Shōni Kagesuke|ja|少弐経資|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, serving as the deputy {{ill|Shugo|ja|守護|qq=draft|qq=draft}} of {{ill|Iki Province|ja|壱岐国|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.
== Biography == In {{ill|Bunei 11|ja|文永11th year|qq=draft|qq=draft}} (1274), during the {{ill|Battle of Bun'ei|ja|文永の役|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, Suketoki made his debut in combat at the age of 12, fighting alongside his uncle, {{ill|Shōni Kagesuke|ja|少弐景資|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. During the {{ill|Battle of Kōan|ja|弘安の役|qq=draft|qq=draft}} in {{ill|Kōan 4|ja|弘安4th year|qq=draft|qq=draft}} (1281), he fought alongside his grandfather {{ill|Shōni Sukenaga|ja|少弐資能|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, his father, and other family members, leading Japanese forces against the {{ill|Eastern Route Army|ja|東路軍|qq=draft|qq=draft}} occupying Iki Island. He died in battle at the age of 19.
Following the defeat of the Eastern Route Army on Iki Island, the Mongol forces retreated to {{ill|Hirado Island|ja|平戸島|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, and later, Shōni Kagesuke annihilated the Mongol forces at {{ill|Takashima (Nagasaki)|ja|鷹島|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. In {{ill|Taishō 4|ja|大正4th year|qq=draft|qq=draft}} (1915), Suketoki was posthumously awarded the Rank of Junior Fourth Rank.
Suketoki is enshrined as a deity at {{ill|Iki Shrine|ja|壱岐神社|qq=draft|qq=draft}} and {{ill|Iki Gokoku Shrine|ja|壱岐護国神社|qq=draft|qq=draft}} in Ashibe Town, Iki City. A stone grave dedicated to him is located in the adjacent Shōni Park, where he is affectionately known as "Shōni-sama."
== Related Historical Sites == * '''Grave of Shōni Suketoki''' (Ashibe Town, Iki City) Located near {{ill|Iki Shrine|ja|壱岐神社|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, the grave is part of "Shōni Park," which also includes a monument commemorating the {{ill|Battle of Kōan|ja|弘安の役|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, anchor stones believed to be from Japanese ships of the period, and a {{ill|smoke signal|ja|狼煙|qq=draft|qq=draft}} station.
<gallery> File:Shoni_Suketoki's_Tomb_in_Shoni_Park,_Ashibe,_Iki,_Nagasaki.jpg|Grave of Shōni Suketoki File:Shoni_Park.jpg|Entrance to Shōni Park File:Koan_no_Eki_Battleplace_in_Iki,_Nagasaki.jpg|Battlefield of the Kōan Campaign File:Anchor_of_the_Middle-age_Japanese_Ship_in_Shoni_Park,_Iki,_Nagasaki.jpg|Anchor stone from the period File:Smoke_Signal_Stand_in_Shoni_Park,_Ashibe,_Iki,_Nagasaki.jpg|Smoke signal station </gallery>
* '''Funakakushi Castle''' {{Section-stub}}
== Additional Information == In {{ill|1997|ja|平成9th year|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, a statue of Shōni Suketoki riding a horse, sculpted by {{ill|Koganemaru Ikku|ja|小金丸幾久|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, was erected in front of the Ashibe Ferry Terminal to commemorate the 720th anniversary of the {{ill|Mongol invasions of Japan|ja|元寇|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.
