{{Infobox samurai | name = Shōni Suketoki | image = Suketoki Shoni Statue.jpg | image_size = 220px | image_caption = Statue of Shōni Suketoki in {{ill|Iki City|ja|壱岐市|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Iki City|qq=}} | era = Mid-{{ill|Kamakura period|ja|鎌倉時代|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kamakura period|qq=}} | birth_date = {{ill|Kōchō 3|ja|弘長3rd year|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kōchō 3|qq=}} (1263) | death_date = {{ill|Kōan 4|ja|弘安4th year|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kōan 4|qq=}} [[June 29 (lunar calendar)|June 29]] (July 16, 1281) | other_names = | posthumous_name = | grave = {{ill|Ashibe Town|ja|芦辺町|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ashibe Town|qq=}}, Iki City, {{ill|Nagasaki Prefecture|ja|長崎県|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nagasaki Prefecture|qq=}} | Rank = {{ill|Governor|ja|権守|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Governor|qq=}} of {{ill|Bitchū Province|ja|備中国|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Bitchū Province|qq=}}, posthumously awarded {{ill|Junior Fourth Rank|ja|従四位|1=Junior Fourth Rank|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Junior Fourth Rank|13=User:Immanuelle/Junior Fourth Rank|qq=}} | allegiance = {{ill|Kamakura Shogunate|ja|鎌倉幕府|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kamakura Shogunate|qq=}}, Deputy {{ill|Shugo|ja|守護|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shugo|qq=}} of {{ill|Iki Province|ja|壱岐国|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Iki Province|qq=}} | master = {{ill|Prince Koreyasu|ja|惟康親王|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Prince Koreyasu|qq=}} | clan = {{ill|Shōni clan|ja|少弐氏|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shōni clan|qq=}} | parents = Father: {{ill|Shōni Kagesuke|ja|少弐経資|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shōni Kagesuke|qq=}} | siblings = Suketoki, {{ill|Shōni Moritsune|ja|少弐盛経|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shōni Moritsune|qq=}}, {{ill|Shōni Tokitsune|ja|少弐時経|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shōni Tokitsune|qq=}}, {{ill|Shōni Morishige|ja|少弐盛氏|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shōni Morishige|qq=}}, {{ill|Shōni Sadatsune|ja|少弐貞資|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shōni Sadatsune|qq=}} | spouse = | children = | notable_battles = {{ill|Mongol invasions of Japan|ja|元寇|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Mongol invasions of Japan|qq=}} ({{ill|Battle of Iki|ja|壱岐島の戦い|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Battle of Iki|qq=}}) }}
'''Shōni Suketoki''' (少弐 資時) was a mid-{{ill|Kamakura period|ja|鎌倉時代|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kamakura period|qq=}} {{ill|samurai|ja|武士|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/samurai|qq=}} and the eldest son of {{ill|Shōni Kagesuke|ja|少弐経資|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shōni Kagesuke|qq=}}, serving as the deputy {{ill|Shugo|ja|守護|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shugo|qq=}} of {{ill|Iki Province|ja|壱岐国|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Iki Province|qq=}}.
== Biography == In {{ill|Bunei 11|ja|文永11th year|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Bunei 11|qq=}} (1274), during the {{ill|Battle of Bun'ei|ja|文永の役|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Battle of Bun'ei|qq=}}, Suketoki made his debut in combat at the age of 12, fighting alongside his uncle, {{ill|Shōni Kagesuke|ja|少弐景資|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shōni Kagesuke|qq=}}. During the {{ill|Battle of Kōan|ja|弘安の役|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Battle of Kōan|qq=}} in {{ill|Kōan 4|ja|弘安4th year|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kōan 4|qq=}} (1281), he fought alongside his grandfather {{ill|Shōni Sukenaga|ja|少弐資能|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shōni Sukenaga|qq=}}, his father, and other family members, leading Japanese forces against the {{ill|Eastern Route Army|ja|東路軍|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Eastern Route Army|qq=}} occupying Iki Island. He died in battle at the age of 19.
Following the defeat of the Eastern Route Army on Iki Island, the Mongol forces retreated to {{ill|Hirado Island|ja|平戸島|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hirado Island|qq=}}, and later, Shōni Kagesuke annihilated the Mongol forces at {{ill|Takashima (Nagasaki)|ja|鷹島|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Takashima (Nagasaki)|qq=}}. In {{ill|Taishō 4|ja|大正4th year|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Taishō 4|qq=}} (1915), Suketoki was posthumously awarded the Rank of Junior Fourth Rank.
Suketoki is enshrined as a deity at {{ill|Iki Shrine|ja|壱岐神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Iki Shrine|qq=}} and {{ill|Iki Gokoku Shrine|ja|壱岐護国神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Iki Gokoku Shrine|qq=}} in Ashibe Town, Iki City. A stone grave dedicated to him is located in the adjacent Shōni Park, where he is affectionately known as "Shōni-sama."
== Related Historical Sites == * '''Grave of Shōni Suketoki''' (Ashibe Town, Iki City) Located near {{ill|Iki Shrine|ja|壱岐神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Iki Shrine|qq=}}, the grave is part of "Shōni Park," which also includes a monument commemorating the {{ill|Battle of Kōan|ja|弘安の役|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Battle of Kōan|qq=}}, anchor stones believed to be from Japanese ships of the period, and a {{ill|smoke signal|ja|狼煙|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/smoke signal|qq=}} station.
<gallery> File:Shoni_Suketoki's_Tomb_in_Shoni_Park,_Ashibe,_Iki,_Nagasaki.jpg|Grave of Shōni Suketoki File:Shoni_Park.jpg|Entrance to Shōni Park File:Koan_no_Eki_Battleplace_in_Iki,_Nagasaki.jpg|Battlefield of the Kōan Campaign File:Anchor_of_the_Middle-age_Japanese_Ship_in_Shoni_Park,_Iki,_Nagasaki.jpg|Anchor stone from the period File:Smoke_Signal_Stand_in_Shoni_Park,_Ashibe,_Iki,_Nagasaki.jpg|Smoke signal station </gallery>
