{{Infobox samurai | name = Shōni Suketoki | image = Suketoki Shoni Statue.jpg | image_size = 220px | image_caption = Statue of Shōni Suketoki in [[:en:Iki, Nagasaki|Iki City]] | era = Mid-[[:en:Kamakura period|Kamakura period]] | birth_date = {{ill|Kōchō 3|ja|弘長3年|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kōchō 3|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} (1263) | death_date = {{ill|Kōan 4|ja|弘安4年|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kōan 4|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} [[June 29 (lunar calendar)|June 29]] (July 16, 1281) | other_names = | posthumous_name = | grave = {{ill|Ashibe Town|ja|芦辺町|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ashibe Town|qq=}}, Iki City, [[:en:Nagasaki Prefecture|Nagasaki Prefecture]] | Rank = {{ill|Governor|ja|権守|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Governor|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 国司|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 国司}} of [[:en:Bitchū Province|Bitchū Province]], posthumously awarded {{ill|Junior Fourth Rank|ja|従四位|1=Junior Fourth Rank|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Junior Fourth Rank|13=User:Immanuelle/Junior Fourth Rank|qq=}} | allegiance = [[:en:Kamakura shogunate|Kamakura Shogunate]], Deputy [[:en:Shugo|Shugo]] of [[:en:Iki Province|Iki Province]] | master = [[:en:Prince Koreyasu|Prince Koreyasu]] | clan = [[:en:Shōni clan|Shōni clan]] | parents = Father: {{ill|Shōni Kagesuke|ja|少弐経資|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shōni Kagesuke|qq=}} | siblings = Suketoki, {{ill|Shōni Moritsune|ja|少弐盛経|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shōni Moritsune|qq=}}, {{ill|Shōni Tokitsune|ja|少弐時経|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shōni Tokitsune|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}, {{ill|Shōni Morishige|ja|少弐盛氏|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shōni Morishige|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}, {{ill|Shōni Sadatsune|ja|少弐貞資|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shōni Sadatsune|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} | spouse = | children = | notable_battles = [[:en:Mongol invasions of Japan|Mongol invasions of Japan]] ({{ill|Battle of Iki|ja|壱岐島の戦い|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Battle of Iki|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}) }}
'''Shōni Suketoki''' (少弐 資時) was a mid-[[:en:Kamakura period|Kamakura period]] {{ill|samurai|ja|武士|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/samurai|qq=}} and the eldest son of {{ill|Shōni Kagesuke|ja|少弐経資|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shōni Kagesuke|qq=}}, serving as the deputy [[:en:Shugo|Shugo]] of [[:en:Iki Province|Iki Province]].
== Biography == In {{ill|Bunei 11|ja|文永11年|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Bunei 11|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} (1274), during the [[:en:Battle of Bun'ei|Battle of Bun'ei]], Suketoki made his debut in combat at the age of 12, fighting alongside his uncle, {{ill|Shōni Kagesuke|ja|少弐景資|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shōni Kagesuke|qq=}}. During the [[:en:Battle of Kōan|Battle of Kōan]] in {{ill|Kōan 4|ja|弘安4年|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kōan 4|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} (1281), he fought alongside his grandfather {{ill|Shōni Sukenaga|ja|少弐資能|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shōni Sukenaga|qq=}}, his father, and other family members, leading Japanese forces against the {{ill|Eastern Route Army|ja|東路軍|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Eastern Route Army|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} occupying Iki Island. He died in battle at the age of 19.
Following the defeat of the Eastern Route Army on Iki Island, the Mongol forces retreated to [[:en:Hirado Island|Hirado Island]], and later, Shōni Kagesuke annihilated the Mongol forces at {{ill|Takashima (Nagasaki)|ja|鷹島|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Takashima (Nagasaki)|qq=}}. In [[:en:1915|Taisho 3]][[Category:Years needing redirect replacements]] (1915), Suketoki was posthumously awarded the Rank of Junior Fourth Rank.
Suketoki is enshrined as a deity at {{ill|Iki Gokoku Shrine|lt=Iki Gokoku Shrine|lt=Iki Shrine|ja|壱岐神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Iki Shrine|qq=}} and {{ill|Iki Gokoku Shrine|ja|壱岐護国神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Iki Gokoku Shrine|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} in Ashibe Town, Iki City. A stone grave dedicated to him is located in the adjacent Shōni Park, where he is affectionately known as "Shōni-sama."
== Related Historical Sites == * '''Grave of Shōni Suketoki''' (Ashibe Town, Iki City) Located near {{ill|Iki Gokoku Shrine|lt=Iki Gokoku Shrine|lt=Iki Shrine|ja|壱岐神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Iki Shrine|qq=}}, the grave is part of "Shōni Park," which also includes a monument commemorating the [[:en:Battle of Kōan|Battle of Kōan]], anchor stones believed to be from Japanese ships of the period, and a [[:en:Smoke signal|smoke signal]] station.
<gallery> File:Shoni_Suketoki's_Tomb_in_Shoni_Park,_Ashibe,_Iki,_Nagasaki.jpg|Grave of Shōni Suketoki File:Shoni_Park.jpg|Entrance to Shōni Park File:Koan_no_Eki_Battleplace_in_Iki,_Nagasaki.jpg|Battlefield of the Kōan Campaign File:Anchor_of_the_Middle-age_Japanese_Ship_in_Shoni_Park,_Iki,_Nagasaki.jpg|Anchor stone from the period File:Smoke_Signal_Stand_in_Shoni_Park,_Ashibe,_Iki,_Nagasaki.jpg|Smoke signal station </gallery>
* '''Funakakushi Castle''' {{Section-stub}}
== Additional Information == In [[:en:1997|Heisei 9]][[Category:Years needing redirect replacements]], a statue of Shōni Suketoki riding a horse, sculpted by {{ill|Koganemaru Ikku|ja|小金丸幾久|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Koganemaru Ikku|qq=}}, was erected in front of the Ashibe Ferry Terminal to commemorate the 720th anniversary of the [[:en:Mongol invasions of Japan|Mongol invasions of Japan]].
